variables.name: ISSUES_TO_GROUPS_BUNDLE_KEY
variables.comment:
* A key used in {@link #getExtras()} to map {@link SafetyCenterIssue} ids to their associated
     * {@link SafetyCenterEntryGroup} ids.

variables.name: STATIC_ENTRIES_TO_IDS_BUNDLE_KEY
variables.comment:
* A key used in {@link #getExtras()} to map {@link SafetyCenterStaticEntry} to their associated * ids. * *

{@link SafetyCenterStaticEntry} are keyed by {@code * SafetyCenterIds.toBundleKey(safetyCenterStaticEntry)}.

methods.name: public SafetyCenterStatus getStatus()
methods.comment: Returns the overall {@link SafetyCenterStatus} of the Safety Center.

methods.name: public List<SafetyCenterIssue> getIssues()
methods.comment: Returns the list of active {@link SafetyCenterIssue} objects in the Safety Center.

methods.name: public List<SafetyCenterEntryOrGroup> getEntriesOrGroups()
methods.comment:
* Returns the structured list of {@link SafetyCenterEntry} and {@link SafetyCenterEntryGroup}
     * objects, wrapped in {@link SafetyCenterEntryOrGroup}.

methods.name: public List<SafetyCenterStaticEntryGroup> getStaticEntryGroups()
methods.comment: Returns the list of {@link SafetyCenterStaticEntryGroup} objects in the Safety Center.

methods.name: public List<SafetyCenterIssue> getDismissedIssues()
methods.comment: Returns the list of dismissed {@link SafetyCenterIssue} objects in the Safety Center.

methods.name: public Bundle getExtras()
methods.comment:
* Returns a {@link Bundle} containing additional information, {@link Bundle#EMPTY} by default. * *

Note: internal state of this {@link Bundle} is not used for {@link Object#equals} and * {@link Object#hashCode} implementation of {@link SafetyCenterData}.
